[center]
[img]http://www.zybez.net/img/skillimg/construction/spiralstairs.gif[/img] [size=20pt][b]Easier, cleaner & better stair system for delta.[/b][/size]

[b]The way delta handled stairs bothered me so much that I today, decided to write a new one.
You simply have to store your stair-Ids in the right array.

- Supports messages (go up or down)
- no more use of process and unneeded variables
- Clean, not handled in 20 spots through your files.[/b][/center]


[size=18pt][b]Step 1:[/b][/size]
[b]Remove everything that has to do with stairs. (search for words like "stair or "stairs" in your source and remove the whole methods)[/b]
[size=8pt][i][b]save the methods somewhere if you want to keep the ids.[/b][/i][/size]


[size=18pt][b]Step 2:[/b][/size]
[b]Open client.java and search for packet 132[/b]
[code=java]
case 132:[/code]

[b]if you scroll a bit down you'll see something similar to this:[/b]
[code=java]
			resetAction(false);
			TurnPlayerTo(objectX, objectY);
			updateRequired = true;
			appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
			long time2 = System.currentTimeMillis();
			if (time2 - globalCooldown[0] <= 50) {
				sM("Action throttled... please wait longer before acting!");
				break;
			}
			if ((xDiff > 5) || (yDiff > 5)) {
				break;
			}
[/code]

[b]under that last bracket add this line:[/b]
