[size=18pt][b]Step 6 (optional):[/b][/size]
[b]Now if you also want to use the dropdown menu for stairs,
so if you click go down, or go up it actually works.

First open up your stairshandler and change:[/b]
[code=java]
private int[] stairChoice = {1748};
[/code]

[b]to this:[/b]
[code=java]
public int[] stairChoice = {1748};
[/code]
This is to make our array visible for other classes.


[b]
Now locate your packets. (usually client.java)[/b]

in your object action 2 & 3 packets, ( case 252 & case 70 )
add this:
[code=java]
for (int stair : getStairs().stairChoice) {
				if (objectID == stair) {
					setAnimation(828);
					toX = absX;
					toY = absY;
					heightLevel ++;
				}
			}
[/code]

[b]But in your 3th object action packet(70) you must change [i]heightlevel ++;[/i] to [i]heightlevel --[/i];[/b]



